sentences: Holger Hiller (born 26 December 1956) is a German musician.
With Fehlmann he later founded the band Palais Schaumburg in 1980, of which he was the singer.
From 1984 on, he lived in London, eventually working as producer for Mute Records.
In 1988, he started a band project called Ohi Ho Bang Bang with video artist Akiko Hada, recording a song/video called "The Two," releasing it as both a 12" single and a CD Video.
Since 2003, Hiller lives in Berlin, working as an English language teacher.
